s and careers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aChoice (Psychology) 0aChoice (Psychology). 0aLife change events. 0aStay-at-home mothers. 0aWork and family. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aamerican culture.  aamerican society.  abankers.  acareer.  acaring for a family.  achildren.  acultural pressures.  acultural studies.  adoctors.  afamily and career.  afamily matters.  afamily.  agender and labor.  agender equality.  agender expectations.  agender norms.  agender studies.  alawyers.  amen and women.  amotherhood.  amothers.  aparenthood.  aprivatized family.  aprofessional women.  apushed out of the workplace.  areturning home.  ascientists.  asociology.  astaying home with kids.  atime demanding jobs.  aunited states of america.  awomen and work.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094179340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520941793423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520941793/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles